In OpenROAD, you can specify the name for a database table using the `name` keyword followed by the desired table name:
```roadsample
database {
  // Database configuration
}
table MyTable {
  // Table properties and columns
  name = "my_table";
}
```
This specifies that the table name is `my_table`. You can use any valid alphanumeric identifier as the name, as long as it adheres to the rules mentioned earlier.
